 "_maintenance_notes": [
  "2026-05-29 R27: probe_dedup_check.py Step-5c was a no-op because the documented BARE command takes the design-time SCAN path and reads empty stdin, never appending (NOT an off-by-one; auto_detect_next_round latest+1 is correct for the scan). FIXED: Step-5c now uses --append-latest + a TTY guard + --self-test. Ledger repopulated via --append-latest (added module_70 missed by the initial manual add; advanced spanned modules to eligible_after=30).",
  "2026-05-30 R30-R32 doc push: appended/advanced 11 module probes (10,09,12,13,55,62 -> elig 33-34; 45,28,58,53,57 -> 35). Non-module docs (cross_module/, core_docs/, reference/, agent/helpers/) audited this push are NOT ledger-tracked (ledger tracks GAMS module/var/eq/realization names only).",
  "2026-07-18 R59 (split QA round): Step 5c handled MANUALLY, not via --append-latest. Two reasons. (1) R59 is a SPLIT round: its questions live under arm_A_fix_verification.questions and arm_B_cold_hubs.questions, but collect_probe_names_from_round() reads round_data[\"questions\"] at the TOP level only -- so --append-latest would have appended NOTHING, silently. Same class as the R27 no-op this file already records as FIXED. (2) PLAN \u00a70/\u00a73 forbids entering Arm A names as FRESH probes: Arm A deliberately re-probed the four docs R58 rewrote hours earlier, so those scores measure \"did the fix hold\", NOT capability. ACTION TAKEN: appended the union of ARM B modules_tested only (Arm B probes were genuine fresh capability probes), via the script's own append_round_to_ledger() so the tested advance/skip logic was reused rather than hand-editing. 14 entries advanced to 62; module_52/module_56 skipped as calibration-exempt. EXCLUDED as Arm-A-only: module_16, module_30, module_70, module_71. NOTE for maintainers: rounds R53-R58 were never appended (ledger was last advanced from R52), so the rotation state remains behind for names not touched by R59. Backfill was OUT OF SCOPE for R59."
 ]
